The article announces the nominations sent to the Senate by the White House. Colin Stirling Bruce is nominated to be the United States District Judge for the Central District of Illinois, replacing Michael P. McCuskey who is retiring. Sara Lee Ellis is nominated to be the United States District Judge for the Northern District of Illinois, replacing Joan B. Gottschall who has retired. Andrea R. Wood is nominated to be the United States District Judge for the Northern District of Illinois, replacing William J. Hibbler who is deceased.